    "recap_headline": "Akron Athletics",
    "recap_text": "YPSILANTI, Mich. -\nFour Akron players recorded multiple hits to help lead the Zips over the Eastern Michigan Eagles 7-3 Friday.\nEaston Amundson\nrecorded two hits, a home run, a run and RBI.\nBrody Chrisman\nhas two hits, a double, a run and an RBI.\nBlake Bowen\nalso recorded a two-hit performance with an RBI while\nKelton Phillips\nhad a triple among his two hits.\nBrady Bowen\n(2-0) got the win out of the bullpen for Akron (10-10, ). The right-hander went 2.2 innings, giving up two runs, both of them earned, on three hits, allowing one walk and striking out two.\nFloyd McKenna\nalso pitched well, going 2.1 shutout innings while allowing one hit, walking none and striking out three.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nTrailing 1-0, the Zips first put runs on the board in the third inning. Akron got an RBI single from freshman\nBrody Chrisman\n, scoring freshman\nKelton Phillips\nfrom third base.\nThe score stayed at 1-1 until the very next inning, when the Zips put runs on the scoreboard once again. Akron picked up a run on freshman\nEaston Amundson's\ntwo-out solo home run off of junior John Carmichael, which brought the Zips lead to 2-1.\nAkron kept Eastern Michigan scoreless before building their lead to 4-1 in the seventh inning. The Zips produced a two-run frame, punctuated with an RBI triple off the bat of freshman\nTucker Biehl\n.\nThe Eagles fought back, closing the gap to 4-3 until Akron added some insurance in the eighth. The Zips scored once on an RBI single off the bat of Phillips, bringing the score to 5-3 in favor of Akron.\nThe Zips kept Eastern Michigan off the board before expanding their lead to 7-3 the following inning. Akron brought home a pair, with one run driven in by freshman\nBlake Bowen's\nsingle. The score remained 7-3 for the rest of the game, as the Zips coasted to the win.\nGAME NOTES\n\u00bb Akron's highest scoring inning was the ninth, when it pushed two runs across.\n\u00bb Four Zips had multiple hits in the ballgame.\n\u00bb The Zips out-hit the Eagles at an 11-7 clip.\n\u00bb The Zips swiped five bases as a team.\n\u00bb Akron pitchers limited Eastern Michigan to just 3-for-15 (.200) with runners in scoring position.\n\u00bb Akron pitchers faced 42 Eastern Michigan hitters in the game, allowing six ground balls and 13 fly balls while striking out seven.\n\u00bb The Zips drew six walks from Eastern Michigan pitching.\nWHAT'S NEXT?\nAkron and Eastern Michigan continue the series on Saturday, March 21, for a 3 p.m. start.",
